parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gauges not working
temperature and gas level indicators not functioning
radio turning off
fans turning off
blind spot warning lights malfunctioning
error messages on the dashboard
and theft deterrent system issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SSDS can cause the blind spot detection system to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: SSDS maintenance light appears on the dashboard
blind spot warning lights malfunctioning
and error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of sensor modules can cause the SSDS to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: SSDS maintenance light appears on the dashboard
blind spot warning lights malfunctioning
and error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless ignition system can cause the vehicle to fail to start or shut off, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Key cannot be removed from the ignition
steering wheel locked
and engine starting independently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the theft deterrent system can cause the vehicle to fail to start or shut off, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Theft deterrent system error messages on the dashboard
and engine starting independently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning passenger occupancy sensor can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, potentially leading to airbag failure in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag is not enabled
the sensor alerts constantly while driving
the airbag light is not lit when a passenger is present
the warning chime sounds constantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the service side detection module can cause the vehicle's systems to shut down, including the anti-theft system, and lead to erratic vehicle behavior, which can increase the risk of accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down
the anti-theft system is enabled
the vehicle drives erratically
voltage error codes are displayed
the service airbag warning is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock striker plate can cause the door to not close correctly, leading to potential safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The door does not close flush
a small gap is present when the door is closed
the door lock striker plate is loose or has pulled away from the doorframe post.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the gearshift can cause difficulty or inability to shift gears, leading to potential safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: The gearshift does not always work
the gearshift needs to be wiggled to function
the gearshift is loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side detection sensors can cause a loss of safety features, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The "Service Side Detection System" message persists
the side detection sensors are inoperative
water is present in the mounting brackets for the sensor modules.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause serious injury or death, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
the entire car is completely burnt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of steering capability, radio and screen malfunction, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The electrical system shuts down
power steering fails
radio and screen shut down
cruise control and blinker malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the loss of steering capability, increase the risk of accidents, and potentially lead to fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
the steering feels like it wants to lock up
the car shakes or shudders between 15-20 mph
the steering wheel and car body shake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak system can cause the loss of steering capability, increase the risk of accidents, and potentially lead to fatalities.
symptoms: The Stabilitrak system requires service
the car jumps lanes and leaves the road
the steering capability is lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the air conditioning to malfunction, increase engine temperatures, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: The air conditioning is off due to high engine temperatures
the error message appears even when the car is first started.
